Name: Elegance Collection
Watch Details: Grand Seiko continues to excel at the apex of Japanese watch-making with a sublime range of techniques and skills that exist nowhere else. The most remarkable aspect of this dress watch from its Elegance collection is the lacquer made from the sap of the urushi trees found under Mount Iwate in northern Japan. The lacquer is mixed with iron to give it its deep, jet-black colour. The GS logo and hour markers for 6 and 12 o’clock are individually crafted by a urushi master who builds up the lacquer to create a 3-D profile before coating with powdered gold and polishing. Within the 39mm 18k rose gold case you’ll find Grand Seiko’s manual-wind Caliber 9S63, which holds a 72-hour power reserve. It’s also limited to just 150 pieces.
